HEADWORD: may apple
<hw>may apple</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>North American herb (<spn>Podophyllum peltatum</spn>)
with poisonous root stock and an edible though insipid egg-shaped
yellowish fruit; called also <altname>wild mandrake</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> May apple, wild mandrake, <spn>Podophyllum
peltatum</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The fruit of the mayapple{1}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

